•	Strong Python engineering skills, including object-oriented design, modular code, packaging, and reusable, maintainable codebases.
	•	Experience handling large-scale transactional datasets, using Pandas, Dask, Polars, or similar distributed data processing frameworks.
	•	Hands-on ML/AI modeling experience, using scikit-learn, PyTorch, Keras, or TensorFlow, with understanding of model metrics, performance, retraining, and model drift.
	•	Experience building Python microservices and APIs, using FastAPI, Flask, or Django, with async IO, Celery, Dockerization, and orchestration using Kubernetes.
	•	Strong delivery, CI/CD, and MLOps experience, including Git and Bitbucket workflows, MLflow or equivalent tools, and managing models from experimentation to production.
	•	Working knowledge of cloud and distributed systems, including AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud, messaging and streaming platforms such as Kafka or RabbitMQ, and diverse data stores.
	•	Strong collaboration and learning mindset, with the ability to work across teams and geographies, adapt to new technologies, mentor others, and take end-to-end ownership.  ———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————

Lead and evolve the end-to-end technical architecture for AML platforms, including Python services, microservices, ML/AI components, data pipelines, asynchronous RESTful and GraphQL APIs, containerized using Docker and orchestrated with Kubernetes in cloud environments.
	•	Design and deliver production-ready Python solutions for large-scale AML systems, handling high-volume transactional data with focus on performance, scalability, security, and regulatory compliance.
	•	Define and enforce Python engineering standards, covering object-oriented design, modular codebases, reusable libraries, and consistent packaging practices.
	•	Drive end-to-end delivery of Python and ML systems, including CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, cloud deployments, and production support.
	•	Own the ML model lifecycle (MLOps) from experimentation to production, ensuring model versioning, monitoring, retraining, and governance using tools such as MLflow or equivalent.
	•	Remain hands-on when required, contributing to model development, feature engineering, experimentation, Python implementation, and production deployment.
	•	Collaborate across engineering, data science, and compliance teams, providing technical leadership, architectural guidance, and end-to-end ownership of AML solutions.
